    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-15T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-15T22:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115/37965: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-15T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>506. Your 3907, November 29.<note n="2" xml:id="d400fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1940v02#pg_176">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 176</ref>.</note> In reference to
                    various requests made to the Embassy by prominent persons and others for its
                    intercession with the British authorities to obtain priority for Americans on
                    the British planes to Lisbon you are informed that to avoid discrimination in
                    view of the fact that a number of Americans in the British Isles desire to use
                    this means of returning to the United States the Department desires the Embassy
                    to request priority only in the case of American officials or others traveling
                    in connection with matters of interest to this Government and in the case of
                    proved serious illness necessitating the prompt evacuation of the individual
                    concerned from the British Isles.</p>
                <p>The Department will so inform all persons seeking its intercession to obtain such
                    priority and the Embassy should similarly reply to any such requests received by
                    it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
